DATA ATTRIBUTION AND LICENSING

The MIT license above covers the repository's code (generators, the
Maho\DirectoryData\Paths shim, and workflow definitions). The data
files are derived from upstream sources with their own licenses, listed below.
Downstream consumers redistributing any of these data files must preserve the
relevant attribution.

1. countries.json and regions/*.json
   Derived from:
   - Debian's iso-codes project: https://salsa.debian.org/iso-codes-team/iso-codes
     Licensed under LGPL-2.1+
   - PHP ISO Codes library (sokil/php-isocodes): https://github.com/sokil/php-isocodes
     Licensed under MIT
   - PHP ISO Codes Database (sokil/php-isocodes-db-i18n): https://github.com/sokil/php-isocodes-db-i18n
     Licensed under MIT

2. formats/*.json
   Derived from Google's libaddressinput Address Data Service:
   https://github.com/google/libaddressinput
   Source endpoint: https://chromium-i18n.appspot.com/ssl-aggregate-address/data/
   Licensed under CC-BY 4.0: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
   Modifications: upstream "data/<CC>" / "data/<CC>/<SUB>" key structure is
   flattened into a "country" / "subdivisions" split per file; all upstream
   fields are preserved verbatim.
